<!-- BARINGS BANK -->
<article class="event" id="event-barings">
  <header>
    <h3><time datetime="1995">1995</time> — Barings Bank</h3>
  </header>
  <p>
    Nick Leeson was simultaneously executing trades and reporting on them from
    Barings' Singapore office — a fundamental separation-of-duties failure. He
    was also generating implausibly consistent profits that should have raised
    immediate questions about how. Nobody in London's management asked
    mechanistic questions. The dashboard — growing profits, a star trader — was
    too comfortable to interrogate. Barings lost £827 million, more than its
    entire capital, and collapsed in 1995. It was Britain's oldest merchant
    bank, established 1762.
  </p>
