<!-- FUKUSHIMA -->
<article class="event" id="event-fukushima">
  <header>
    <h3>
      <time datetime="2011-03-11">11 March 2011</time> — Fukushima Daiichi
    </h3>
  </header>
  <p>
    The tsunami risk to the Fukushima Daiichi plant had been assessed and raised
    internally. The seawall height was based on historical records that excluded
    the most extreme events in the geological record. Prior survivals — previous
    smaller earthquakes and tsunamis — had created confidence. When the 2011
    Tōhoku earthquake generated a tsunami far exceeding design parameters, the
    seawall was overtopped, backup diesel generators flooded, and three reactor
    cores melted down. The knowledge that the design basis tsunami was too
    conservative had been present in the system. It did not change the decision.
  </p>
